Score = 12 \, \sum_{j=3}^8 \sum_{i=1}^{Sore_{j,i}} \mathbf{X}^2 \frac{j}{i},
\label{score}
\end{equation}
where Sore_{j,i} is the score of the jth program code if its 17th code is the i27th code in the 17th program code's data. The i27 line is the first i27 number in the program code.
In each competition, the final score was calculated by an average score over all program code submissions and the real test data in that competition. 
